VII. SERVIUS TULLIUS, THE SIXTH KING OF THE ROMANS.

Page 12. 1. Servius Tullius: according to the universal tradition Servius was of Latin origin. The story of his career is full of marvels, and cannot be regarded as history. The tradition may point to a successful attempt of the Latins to throw off the yoke of the Etruscans, who, however, afterwards reconquered them. The constitution ascribed to Servius goes back to very early times, it endured with some modifications until the fall of the Republic.
